710. The Romans erected many palatial buildings at Baiae, the foundations of which osten extended into the sea. The fall of Bitias is compared to masses of rock thrown into the sea for such foundations. 717-818. Mars now inspires the enemy with fresh courage, and unnerves the Trojans. Pandarus closes the gate, and in doing this shuts in Turnus, whom he at once assaiIS, incited by his brother's death. Pandarus is slain, and Turnus then attacks the daunted Trojans. He is soon surrounded, but finally saves himself by plunging from the battlements into the Tiber, whence he hastens to join his countrymen.
